1
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:12,533
<i> Everybody, put your hands up!</i>

2
00:00:15,267 --> 00:00:16,400
<i> Organs...</i>

3
00:00:16,533 --> 00:00:17,833
<i> Organ harvesting...</i>

4
00:00:17,967 --> 00:00:19,367
<i> Reign.</i>

5
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:20,333
<i> Reign, wake up.</i>

6
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:21,900
<i> Sir, you take care of Reign.</i>

7
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:23,067
<i> I'll just look for Sir Tonyo.</i>

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:23,967
<i> Okay.</i>

9
00:00:37,367 --> 00:00:42,300
<i>You're ruining everything
I've worked hard for!</i>

10
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:53,800
<i>For sure, they will be
in trouble with the chief.</i>

11
00:00:53,933 --> 00:00:55,200
<i> Disobeying direct orders?</i>

12
00:00:55,467 --> 00:00:56,500
<i>There's a sanction for that
when they get home.</i>

13
00:00:56,733 --> 00:00:58,133
<i> I'm sure Conde knows that.</i>

14
00:00:58,267 --> 00:00:59,700
<i>He just can't leave Enriquez
behind.</i>

15
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:01,133
<i> Believe me, Chief.</i>

16
00:01:01,267 --> 00:01:02,300
<i> It's really just me.</i>

17
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:04,167
<i>So I hope you'll just
suspend me.</i>

18
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:06,967
<i>Sir, you don't have to cover
for us with the chief.</i>

19
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,933
I just don't want to burden
the whole Station 12.

20
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:10,667
<i>You'd better get
your people ready.</i>

21
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,167
<i> Because after the elections,</i>

22
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:15,300
<i>I want you to finish off
Enriquez and Conde.</i>

23
00:01:15,567 --> 00:01:17,667
<i> Did I hear that right?</i>

24
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:20,533
<i>You're going to finish off
Sergeant Enriquez</i>

25
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:22,433
<i> and Lieutenant Conde?</i>

26
00:01:25,433 --> 00:01:26,533
Dad, I didn't know you're there.

27
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:30,100
No, I was just talking
to Station 12,

28
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:32,067
and I told them that

29
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:36,333
I hope they finish whatever
mission Lieutenant Conde

30
00:01:36,467 --> 00:01:38,533
and Sergeant Enriquez
were given abroad,

31
00:01:38,667 --> 00:01:41,500
because I feel more secure
when they're here in Calabari.

32
00:01:41,667 --> 00:01:45,633
The election is coming, and
we need good police officers.

33
00:01:45,767 --> 00:01:47,433
Actually, you're right
about that.

34
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:54,067
They're the reason why the bad
guys here in Calabari go crazy.

35
00:01:55,967 --> 00:01:56,933
Anyway...

36
00:01:57,733 --> 00:02:00,100
okay, I'll go ahead.

37
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:01,633
I still have to attend
to something.

38
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:24,200
Wow!

39
00:02:26,433 --> 00:02:27,867
Idols!

40
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:30,900
Markus has already been
caught...

41
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:34,633
and Selena and your godsister
were saved.

42
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:36,400
You know, no matter how
many times I questioned you

43
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:37,900
when you were abroad,

44
00:02:38,167 --> 00:02:39,100
you did a good job.

45
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,233
Solid police work.

46
00:02:41,733 --> 00:02:43,233
Congratulations,
Lieutenant Conde...

47
00:02:43,367 --> 00:02:44,200
Thank you, Sir.

48
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:45,733
- Sergeant Enriquez.
- Thank you, Sir.

49
00:02:48,533 --> 00:02:51,767
But, Sir, let's not forget
about Lieutenant Garcia as well.

50
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:52,767
Of course...

51
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:56,467
but he asked if he could extend
his stay in Switzerland,

52
00:02:56,733 --> 00:02:58,600
so I let him go

53
00:02:59,133 --> 00:03:00,867
because we disturbed him
during his vacation.

54
00:03:01,267 --> 00:03:02,900
I really idolize
Sergeant Enriquez

55
00:03:03,033 --> 00:03:04,433
and Lieutenant Conde!

56
00:03:04,567 --> 00:03:06,267
Yeah, that's right!

57
00:03:07,467 --> 00:03:09,933
Lieutenant, maybe you can buy
some stir-fry noodles for us.

58
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:13,633
Please, Sir?

59
00:03:13,767 --> 00:03:15,567
Okay, we'll treat you all later.

60
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:17,533
There you go!

61
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:19,533
Sir, bring some soft drinks
with you!

62
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:20,700
Sergeant Enriquez...

63
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:26,733
I'm sure your Godmother Dina
is so proud of you.

64
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:29,567
Thank you, Sir.

65
00:03:30,867 --> 00:03:32,133
Okay, back to work!

66
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:33,333
Yes, Sir!

67
00:03:33,467 --> 00:03:35,000
Just wait for the stir-fry
noodles later, okay?

68
00:03:35,133 --> 00:03:37,867
There you go!

69
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:39,267
I'll go ahead, Sir.

70
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:40,767
Enriquez...

71
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,667
are you okay?

72
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,700
I'm sorry, Sir.

73
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:53,933
I don't understand
what I'm feeling right now.

74
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,600
For the first time,

75
00:03:58,167 --> 00:04:00,933
I did something right
for Godmother Dina's family.

76
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:08,733
Excuse me, Sir.

77
00:04:43,933 --> 00:04:48,967
We still don't know who Amo's
spy is here in Station 12.

78
00:04:51,433 --> 00:04:56,233
So I'll have you finish all
the cases connected to Amo.

79
00:04:58,467 --> 00:05:03,500
That's good, Chief, so we can
control all the information.

80
00:05:03,667 --> 00:05:05,133
But take a break first.

81
00:05:06,700 --> 00:05:08,267
I know you're tired.

82
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:11,133
Tomorrow, we'll go through
everything we have.

83
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:15,067
I'm proud of you.

84
00:05:16,033 --> 00:05:16,833
Good job.

85
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:19,300
Thank you, Sir.

86
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:20,167
You can go ahead.

87
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:21,300
Thank you, Sir.

88
00:05:24,433 --> 00:05:26,633
In fairness to the police
officers who were with us,

89
00:05:26,767 --> 00:05:28,033
they're so handsome!

90
00:05:28,167 --> 00:05:29,833
True, but they're so...

91
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:31,800
snobbish.

92
00:05:31,933 --> 00:05:33,033
They're so aloof.

93
00:05:33,167 --> 00:05:35,467
You know, I hope we can be
with them again.

94
00:05:35,633 --> 00:05:36,233
Oh!

95
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,700
I thought of a way to see
them again.

96
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:41,700
Are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

97
00:05:43,233 --> 00:05:46,500
I hope Captain Isang
gets kidnapped again!

98
00:05:46,633 --> 00:05:47,333
Ouch.

99
00:05:47,467 --> 00:05:48,500
- Ouch.
- What's that?

100
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:49,700
- Why?
- You're being silly again.

101
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:50,500
It's just a joke, Captain.

102
00:05:50,633 --> 00:05:51,433
Is that a joke?

103
00:05:51,567 --> 00:05:53,433
You want me
to be kidnapped again

104
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:56,100
so you can see
some handsome guys?

105
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,400
Yes.

106
00:05:57,533 --> 00:05:58,367
Why?

107
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,733
You really have the audacity
to laugh?

108
00:05:59,867 --> 00:06:02,267
I won't let that happen again,
Grandmother.

109
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:05,100
They'll have to go through me
before they get to you.

110
00:06:05,233 --> 00:06:06,333
My grandchild!

111
00:06:06,467 --> 00:06:07,900
Oh, my!

112
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:09,733
- Bobby!
- Bobby!

113
00:06:09,867 --> 00:06:10,833
Grandmother!

114
00:06:10,967 --> 00:06:12,067
We missed you.

115
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:12,967
Yes.

116
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:13,767
- Grandmother...
- My grandchild...

117
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:16,733
Thank God you're here already.

118
00:06:16,867 --> 00:06:20,133
Sorry, Grandmother,
that you got involved.

119
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:22,933
No, no, it's okay.

120
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,567
The important thing is
that you're here

121
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,900
and we're together again.

122
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:30,767
Mar, Abdul, thank you very much
for saving my grandmother.

123
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,100
Oh my, it's nothing, Bobby.

124
00:06:32,233 --> 00:06:33,467
I hope Captain Isang
gets kidnapped again.

125
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,467
Yes, we're just waiting for her
to be kidnapped again.

126
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,967
- What?
- There you go again.

127
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:37,000
There you go again.

128
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:38,233
Stop it.

129
00:06:38,367 --> 00:06:39,333
My grandchild is here.

130
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:40,667
Oh my...

131
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:41,600
The...

132
00:06:41,767 --> 00:06:43,700
I just got excited.

133
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:45,767
- We missed you, Bobby.
- Yes.

134
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:50,467
Grandmother, the one we caught
abroad, the kidnapper...

135
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,267
he and his lawyer
have already admitted

136
00:06:52,567 --> 00:06:54,867
that Amo is the mastermind
behind everything,

137
00:06:55,133 --> 00:06:59,267
from the museum thefts
to the San Isidro bank robbery.

138
00:06:59,533 --> 00:07:01,333
Does that mean you'll be able
to bring justice

139
00:07:01,467 --> 00:07:02,733
to your Godmother Dina?

140
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,667
She'd be happy.

141
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:11,400
Grandmother, I'm going to
prioritize my promotion too.

142
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:14,467
I'm also going to take the exam
to become a Lieutenant.

143
00:07:14,633 --> 00:07:15,033
Wow!

144
00:07:15,167 --> 00:07:16,233
Perfect, right?

145
00:07:16,367 --> 00:07:20,767
Oh my, your mother
and godmother will be so happy.

146
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:24,233
I missed you, Grandmother...

147
00:07:24,367 --> 00:07:25,633
Before I forget,

148
00:07:25,767 --> 00:07:29,900
how were you and Sir Tonyo
when you were abroad?

149
00:07:33,167 --> 00:07:34,800
<i> You already went to Dubai.</i>

150
00:07:35,033 --> 00:07:37,700
<i>Now, we're here in Milan
to save your godsister.</i>

151
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:39,733
<i> You did everything, Enriquez.</i>

152
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,733
<i>I'm sure your Godmother
Dina would appreciate it.</i>

153
00:07:42,867 --> 00:07:43,567
<i> Enriquez...</i>

154
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:45,867
<i> be careful.</i>

155
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,733
<i> I should also thank you.</i>

156
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:48,933
<i> What for?</i>

157
00:07:49,267 --> 00:07:51,300
<i>Because of you, I remembered
why I became a police officer,</i>

158
00:07:51,433 --> 00:07:53,667
<i>because I want to fight
for what's right</i>

159
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:56,367
<i>and protect everyone
I care about.</i>

160
00:07:58,733 --> 00:08:00,033
It's okay, Grandmother.

161
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:03,333
Lieutenant Conde is a great cop.

162
00:08:03,467 --> 00:08:05,767
Oh my God, Bobby! That's it?

163
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:06,733
You're so stingy
with your answers.

164
00:08:06,867 --> 00:08:08,233
We want the details.

165
00:08:08,367 --> 00:08:09,433
- Details?
- Of course.

166
00:08:09,567 --> 00:08:10,933
Did you sleep next
to each other?

167
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:14,300
Did you shower together?

168
00:08:14,433 --> 00:08:15,833
What are you talking about?

169
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:16,567
Wrong!

170
00:08:17,867 --> 00:08:18,967
You showered together?

171
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:21,100
Grandmother, what's with you?

172
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:22,167
No!

173
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,100
You slept together?

174
00:08:24,233 --> 00:08:25,133
- Did you sleep together?
- No, Grandmother.

175
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:26,633
Come on, let's go home.

176
00:08:26,767 --> 00:08:28,400
Just admit it already.

177
00:08:28,533 --> 00:08:30,067
Stop it, you two.

178
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:32,667
Come on, come on.
I'll cook for you. Let's go.

179
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:33,467
Us first.

180
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,367
- No, us first.
- Us first.

181
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,033
- You're not included.
- You should be kidnapped.

182
00:08:37,167 --> 00:08:38,200
It should be you.

183
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,333
- Hey, Boss Tonyo!
- Boss Tonyo!

184
00:08:44,467 --> 00:08:46,100
- Hey, Lee, Bal.
- How are you, Boss?

185
00:08:46,233 --> 00:08:46,933
What? How are you?

186
00:08:47,067 --> 00:08:48,300
Boss, we're fine.

187
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:50,200
Too bad, he's not here.

188
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:52,767
You haven't seen the heroism
we've shown.

189
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:53,967
We've done something different,
Boss.

190
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,233
- We were really up against...
- It was a big fight.

191
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:59,300
Oh my, I heard about that.

192
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:01,767
So thank you very much.

193
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:05,033
You don't know how important
what you did was

194
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:08,000
for us to complete
the mission abroad.

195
00:09:08,133 --> 00:09:09,933
So is that it, Boss?

196
00:09:10,067 --> 00:09:10,633
Yeah, right.

197
00:09:10,767 --> 00:09:12,233
I feel thirsty, Boss.

198
00:09:12,367 --> 00:09:13,667
- It's hot today.
- Yes, it is.

199
00:09:16,233 --> 00:09:17,633
Okay, okay, drinks
are on me later!

200
00:09:17,767 --> 00:09:18,933
Yes!

201
00:09:19,067 --> 00:09:19,800
That's what we're waiting for!

202
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:20,900
Boss, by the way,

203
00:09:21,033 --> 00:09:23,000
how have you and Ma'am Bobby
been while abroad?

204
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,733
<i> Thank you, Sir. Thank you.</i>

205
00:09:43,367 --> 00:09:45,567
<i>If it weren't for you
and Lieutenant Garcia,</i>

206
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:47,333
<i>I wouldn't have been able
to save my godsister.</i>

207
00:09:47,467 --> 00:09:49,233
<i> So, thank you, Sir.</i>

208
00:09:51,467 --> 00:09:52,867
We enjoyed it.

209
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,400
Dubai, Switzerland, and Italy
are really beautiful.

210
00:09:56,533 --> 00:09:56,900
Hey, in...

211
00:09:57,033 --> 00:09:57,800
in Italy, Boss?

212
00:09:57,933 --> 00:09:59,200
Do you know where Italy
came from?

213
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:03,100
When Lapu-Lapu's ship docked,
he said, "Tie it."

214
00:10:03,267 --> 00:10:05,167
- Tie the ship?
- Yes, tie it.

215
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,067
That's true, Boss,

216
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:07,800
because when Lapu-Lapu
went there,

217
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:10,367
he said to the kid from there...

218
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:11,633
- "Tie it."
- Italian.

219
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:14,633
That's how Italians got their
name, that's how it began.

220
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:16,167
Okay, tell the turtle about it.

221
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:17,567
Tell the...

222
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:19,200
Tell the turtle about it?

223
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:20,733
Do you have a shell?

224
00:10:20,867 --> 00:10:22,100
I don't.

225
00:10:22,233 --> 00:10:23,867
How can I tell the story to him
if he doesn't have a shell?

226
00:10:28,567 --> 00:10:30,833
Amo's hearing will begin
in 2 days.

227
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:36,567
I hope we can close the other
cases we have,

228
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:41,333
like the museum theft
and the San Isidro bank robbery.

229
00:10:41,467 --> 00:10:42,033
Sir...

230
00:10:42,533 --> 00:10:45,167
there are a lot of references
to Amo's movie,

231
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:47,900
the masks, the strychnine,

232
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:51,600
and the bullet in Bullet's
head came from Amo's gun.

233
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:54,933
Conde, what are you thinking?

234
00:10:55,067 --> 00:10:56,900
Sir, we need to talk to Markus.

235
00:10:58,967 --> 00:11:02,867
I think he's the one who
will connect all the cases.

236
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:23,833
I'll be direct to the point,
Markus.

237
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:27,433
With the amount of evidence and
witnesses we have against you,

238
00:11:28,233 --> 00:11:33,133
reclusion perpetua
or life imprisonment,

239
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:35,667
that's what awaits you.

240
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:42,833
But if you cooperate with us,
your sentence can be reduced.

241
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,833
12 to 20 years.

242
00:11:44,967 --> 00:11:46,533
Is that right, Lieutenant Conde?

243
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:48,967
Right.

244
00:11:52,767 --> 00:11:55,133
You just need to tell us

245
00:11:55,267 --> 00:11:59,667
who your mastermind is
in Selena's kidnapping.

246
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:04,600
I'll only talk to the lawyer.

247
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:08,800
Markus,

248
00:12:09,567 --> 00:12:14,567
tell us who tipped you off about
where Selena's safehouse is.

249
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:23,233
I'll only talk to the lawyer.

250
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:27,400
Are you really going
to waste the chance

251
00:12:27,533 --> 00:12:28,667
of getting your sentence reduced

252
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:31,100
just to protect your mastermind?

253
00:12:34,067 --> 00:12:37,400
I'll only talk to the lawyer.

254
00:12:45,267 --> 00:12:47,100
Have you talked to Markus?

255
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:50,300
Yes, Sir, but we're really
getting nothing.

256
00:12:50,767 --> 00:12:53,533
If we don't get a solid
connection to Victor

257
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,700
in the San Isidro bank robbery,

258
00:12:55,833 --> 00:12:57,933
we might not be able
to solve this.

259
00:12:58,333 --> 00:13:02,033
Sir, I think one of us
tipped Markus off

260
00:13:02,167 --> 00:13:04,400
about how to find Selena's
safehouse.

261
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:06,067
We need to catch Roman.

262
00:13:06,767 --> 00:13:08,633
I feel like he's the key
to all of this.

263
00:13:08,767 --> 00:13:10,767
We don't know where Roman is.

264
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,500
Maybe he's gone far away.

265
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:14,333
Enriquez...

266
00:13:15,567 --> 00:13:17,967
can you please get the files
on my desk?

267
00:13:19,233 --> 00:13:20,233
Sure, Sir.

268
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:29,933
What's your plan, Conde?

269
00:13:30,067 --> 00:13:31,767
You might not like it.

270
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:51,233
Wake up.

271
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,233
We're going somewhere.

272
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:55,967
Get in.

273
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:57,467
There you go.

274
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:00,333
Where are you taking me?

275
00:14:02,767 --> 00:14:04,000
Just relax.

276
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:08,133
Let's just go for a stroll.

277
00:14:08,267 --> 00:14:09,333
Hello, Dizon?

278
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:46,633
What are you going to do
with me?

279
00:14:46,767 --> 00:14:49,267
I've run out of options for you,
Markus.

280
00:14:50,733 --> 00:14:52,600
It seems like you're not going
to admit it either.

281
00:14:54,433 --> 00:14:55,600
So I'll kill this guy.

282
00:14:55,733 --> 00:14:58,667
What you're planning
isn't right, Conde.

283
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,233
Don't interfere!

284
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:01,833
You stay there, Dizon.

285
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:02,900
Keep an eye.

286
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:05,667
If anything happens here,
I'm out of it, okay?

287
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:10,633
Keep an eye out there.

288
00:15:17,967 --> 00:15:19,767
Pray now, Markus...

289
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:24,000
because this is your end.

290
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,433
You're still lucky.

291
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:44,967
Hello?

292
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,133
What, Dizon?

293
00:15:49,967 --> 00:15:52,433
You'll hear when it's over.

294
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:54,100
Keep an eye out there!

295
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,733
Where were we?

296
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:02,233
There...

297
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:05,200
Say goodbye already.

298
00:16:26,267 --> 00:16:26,733
Bro...

299
00:16:27,867 --> 00:16:29,533
Bro, let's go. Markus is gone.

300
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:37,133
What?

301
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:39,333
Was it convincing?

302
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,567
Yes. Your acting was superb.

303
00:16:44,267 --> 00:16:45,533
That hurts.

304
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:49,633
Good thing he didn't notice you
were wearing a bulletproof vest.

305
00:16:52,633 --> 00:16:56,000
<i>Is that why you let
Enriquez out?</i>

306
00:16:58,467 --> 00:17:00,567
<i> Well, we know Enriquez, Sir.</i>

307
00:17:01,667 --> 00:17:05,000
<i>I'm sure she won't approve
the plan.</i>

308
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:07,600
<i>So Dizon and I will work alone.</i>

309
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:10,833
<i> Sir, I'll let Markus out.</i>

310
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:16,000
<i>I'll pretend that I'm going
to kill him,</i>

311
00:17:16,167 --> 00:17:17,567
<i> but I'll just let him escape.</i>

312
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:23,567
<i> I'm sure...</i>

313
00:17:24,667 --> 00:17:26,367
<i> he'll go to Roman first.</i>

314
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:27,033
<i> Okay.</i>

315
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:29,767
<i> Just be careful.</i>

316
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:32,033
Go ahead, report to the chief.
Call him.

317
00:17:37,433 --> 00:17:38,167
Hello, Dizon.

318
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:39,633
Any news?

319
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:41,933
Sir, Markus is gone,
the plan worked.

320
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:43,833
We'll track the motorcycle now.

321
00:17:46,367 --> 00:17:47,567
Stay put for now, okay?

322
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:48,967
Wait for backup.

323
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:49,700
Copy, Sir.

324
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:53,600
He hasn't gotten far yet.

325
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:57,133
Let's go.

326
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:12,833
Where is Roman?

327
00:18:14,267 --> 00:18:15,133
Call him!

328
00:18:15,533 --> 00:18:16,367
Call him!

329
00:18:17,067 --> 00:18:17,667
Boss!

330
00:18:19,167 --> 00:18:20,000
Boss!

331
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:31,000
Markus, what are you doing here?

332
00:18:31,133 --> 00:18:32,267
How did you escape?

333
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:34,567
Conde got me out.

334
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:37,767
That fool was planning to
kill me just to get me to talk.

335
00:18:38,567 --> 00:18:39,333
It's Roman.

336
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:44,067
Does that mean
he's Amo's henchman?

337
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:52,067
From Dubai, Italy,
and Switzerland,

338
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:54,100
they're bringing me trouble.

339
00:18:55,000 --> 00:19:00,067
But they won't be a problem now
because I've killed Conde.

340
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:03,933
Let's not talk here.

341
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:06,733
Get some coffee first.

342
00:19:08,733 --> 00:19:09,533
Stay alert.

343
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,800
Drink some coffee first.
I've already talked to the boss.

344
00:19:21,467 --> 00:19:22,400
What?

345
00:19:22,533 --> 00:19:23,767
Can you help me?

346
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:24,667
That's the...

347
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,167
I really need to leave
the country.

348
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:27,567
That's the problem, Markus.

349
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:30,367
If only Selena testifies,
Victor might not be convicted.

350
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:31,567
What?

351
00:19:31,933 --> 00:19:33,067
What do you mean?

352
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:35,567
I can't go back inside, Roman!

353
00:19:35,700 --> 00:19:37,133
- Are you crazy?
- Look at this, look at this!

354
00:19:37,867 --> 00:19:38,633
Did you see this?

355
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:42,267
We're still gathering more
evidence against Victor.

356
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:45,967
But if only one person testifies
against him and no one else...

357
00:19:47,233 --> 00:19:48,233
he might use that
as his defense,

358
00:19:48,367 --> 00:19:49,067
he might get away with it.

359
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:50,300
That's why you shouldn't
run away.

360
00:19:50,433 --> 00:19:53,033
You're crazy if you think
I'll agree to your plan.

361
00:19:54,633 --> 00:19:56,833
Markus, let's not make this
any bigger, okay?

362
00:19:57,567 --> 00:20:00,100
Do your part.
Trust the boss' plan.

363
00:20:00,867 --> 00:20:02,600
I'll get you out myself.

364
00:20:03,233 --> 00:20:04,200
Wait a second.

365
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:06,000
Don't fool me, okay?

366
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:08,067
Yeah, whatever you say.

367
00:20:19,567 --> 00:20:20,733
You're an animal, Roman!

368
00:20:20,867 --> 00:20:23,767
If you think your plan is right,
you're the one who should do it!

369
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:25,267
You're the one who should go
to jail!

370
00:20:30,733 --> 00:20:31,667
You're being followed!

371
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:33,433
Plant this in your brain.

372
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:35,600
It's better to have the boss
indebted to you...

373
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:39,133
than the other way around.
So think about it.

374
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:46,800
Hands up!

375
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:51,167
I said hands up!

376
00:21:51,867 --> 00:21:53,467
It seems you've got me now, Sir.

377
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:55,433
You're really cool.

378
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:59,667
Put your hands up!

379
00:22:22,967 --> 00:22:23,600
Bok...

380
00:22:40,133 --> 00:22:40,867
Sir...

381
00:22:41,267 --> 00:22:44,067
that's the evidence we got
from Markus' hideout.

382
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:47,867
It looks like the money will be
used for Amo's campaign.

383
00:22:50,933 --> 00:22:54,267
This is the solid evidence
we have.

384
00:22:55,733 --> 00:22:59,367
Even if you didn't catch Roman,
it's still mission accomplished.

385
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:02,533
And with the help
of Markus' testimony,

386
00:23:02,667 --> 00:23:07,700
I'm sure Victor Santiago will be
held accountable by the law.

387
00:23:09,767 --> 00:23:11,367
Good job, Dizon.

388
00:23:11,633 --> 00:23:12,300
Thank you, Sir.

389
00:23:13,067 --> 00:23:14,067
Good job, Conde.

390
00:23:20,533 --> 00:23:23,500
Sir, why didn't you include me
in your operation?

391
00:23:25,633 --> 00:23:27,233
I'm sorry, Enriquez.

392
00:23:27,367 --> 00:23:29,767
I thought you might not be able
to follow through with the plan.

393
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:32,233
Really now, Sir?

394
00:23:32,833 --> 00:23:35,667
After everything we've been
through abroad,

395
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:37,833
am I still not going
to trust you now?

396
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:39,633
Enriquez...

397
00:23:41,133 --> 00:23:42,100
we just wanted to make sure.

398
00:23:43,967 --> 00:23:44,900
Don't worry...

399
00:23:45,333 --> 00:23:46,600
I'll make it up to you
next time.

400
00:23:49,967 --> 00:23:51,233
How was your operation?

401
00:23:52,567 --> 00:23:53,533
Any news yet?

402
00:23:53,667 --> 00:23:56,933
Have you got any solid evidence
against Amo?

403
00:23:59,267 --> 00:23:59,967
Yes, we have.

404
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:04,133
So, does that mean
we can put Amo in jail now?

405
00:24:31,667 --> 00:24:35,433
The goal is to identify the
seller of the pimple patches

406
00:24:35,567 --> 00:24:36,200
at school.

407
00:24:36,333 --> 00:24:37,600
So let's blend in for now.

408
00:24:37,733 --> 00:24:39,467
It's better for both of us
to keep a low profile.

409
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:40,767
What's our next move?

410
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:42,233
Kill Markus.

411
00:24:42,367 --> 00:24:44,233
Markus was killed last night.

412
00:24:44,367 --> 00:24:45,433
What?

413
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:48,100
With Markus' death, will
our case against Amo weaken?

414
00:24:48,233 --> 00:24:49,133
Not really, Enriquez,

415
00:24:49,267 --> 00:24:52,333
because we have a lot
of evidence against Amo.

416
00:24:52,467 --> 00:24:55,267
What do you think our next case
will be?

417
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:58,100
I'm going to start ruling
here in Calabari.

418
00:24:58,233 --> 00:24:59,467
What's the update on Jane Doe?

419
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:00,667
She has been identified, Sir.

420
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,100
She's Shaira Reyes.

421
00:25:02,267 --> 00:25:05,033
Sir, do you think we can get any
information from this person?

422
00:25:05,167 --> 00:25:08,200
I'm still not sure,
but I hope she cooperates.
